attributes.llm.system:
You classify user messages into exactly two types:
1. "workflow" — the user wants a multi-step PROCESS: development, debugging, project setup, planning, migration, deployment, refactoring, investigation. These imply structured work with multiple coordinated steps.
2. "direct" — everything else: greetings, questions, single requests, creative tasks, lookups, conversations, simple commands.

If the type is "workflow", also include a "category" field if obvious (e.g. "development", "debugging", "setup", "planning", "migration", "deployment", "refactoring").

Reply with ONLY a JSON object. Examples:
{"type": "direct"}
{"type": "workflow", "category": "development"}
{"type": "workflow", "category": "debugging"}
{"type": "direct"}

